Review_body:
While I write this review, I have about 40 Christmas-specific movies. I include films with Christmas as a 'background' like 'While You Were Sleeping' (1995) and 'Die Hard' (1988), as well as 'Christmas Themed' movies like this one, or the gazillion movies filmed each year for the Hallmark & Lifetime networks.It seems that people view this movie as some kind of special exemption from common sense. This film has a current rating of 7.6... Yeah, um... First Blood (1982) has a current rating of 7.7. One of these rating is obviously very wrong, because these films do not compare on any critical level. The Bridges of Madison County (1995) has a current IMDB rating of 7.6... I resent the hell out of 'Christmas Vacation' (1989) for the way people rave about it's dated and mean-spirited humor, as well as for it's irrationally inflated IMDB rating.On it's own, this film cannot even score a 5 on any critical scale. I gave it an extra point for being culturally significant - people still go to theaters to see this film every year. Ridiculous. I can acknowledge the popularity, but I cannot call this a good film. A Generous 5, and a Merry Christmas to you and yours.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
Acting - 1/1;
Casting - 1/1;
Directing - 1/1;
Story - 1/1;
Writing/Screenplay - 0.5/1;Total Base Score = 4.5Modifiers (+ or -):
Believability/Consistency: -1;Quotability: +0.5;Cultural Significance: +1;Total RealReview Rating: 5
